TITLE: Passed over for another business opportunity? It may be because of your accent
SUMMARY: Globally, nearly one in five workers say they've been passed over for business trips because of the way they speak, according to a survey.

TITLE: F1 Academy: All 10 F1 teams to have drivers and liveries for 2024 season in all-female single-seater series
SUMMARY: "First and foremost, I want to thank the Formula 1 teams for their support and vision as we embark on this journey together," said managing director Susie Wolff.

TITLE: CNBC Daily Open: Powell’s conference had something for everyone
SUMMARY: At his post-meeting press conference, Chair Jerome Powell deftly negotiated expectations from market bulls and bears, somehow affirming both camps.

TITLE: Fed approves hike that takes interest rates to highest level in more than 22 years
SUMMARY: The quarter percentage point move takes the federal funds rate to a target range of 5.25%-5.5%.

TITLE: Samsung reports 95% drop in profit, but expects global demand to recover in second half of the year
SUMMARY: Samsung is the world's largest maker of dynamic random-access memory chips, which are found in consumer devices such as smartphones and computers.

TITLE: Volkswagen buys stake in Xpeng, will jointly develop two new EVs with the Chinese automaker
SUMMARY: The new EVs, which will be branded as VWs and sold only in China, are expected to launch in 2026.

TITLE: Nissan CEO spots key to cracking 'challenging' China market after demand slump
SUMMARY: Makoto Uchida told CNBC delivering new products at speed would be key as the company reported a fall in sales and declining market share.

TITLE: The Dow just posted its best winning streak since the 1980s. Why it keeps going higher
SUMMARY: The Dow on Wednesday rose for a 13th straight day, matching its longest winning streak since 1987.

TITLE: What happened to the Chinese travel boom everyone was waiting for? It stayed in China
SUMMARY: Rather than a boom, the recovery of international travel in China is likely to be spread out over 2023 and 2024, says Mastercard economist David Mann.

TITLE: A vital system of ocean currents could collapse much sooner than expected, scientists warn
SUMMARY: Scientists have previously sounded the alarm over studies showing a rapid slowdown of the Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation.

TITLE: Facebook's ad rebound gives Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg freedom to pursue far-out bets
SUMMARY: Meta's improved financial picture is allowing the company to invest in the money-losing metaverse, while rival Snap is under increased pressure.

TITLE: Meta reports better-than-expected results and issues optimistic guidance for third quarter
SUMMARY: Meta said revenue in the quarter increased 11% as the company returned to double-digit growth for the first time since late 2021.

TITLE: Samsung launches two new folding smartphones to fend off competition from rivals
SUMMARY: Samsung on Wednesday launched two new folding smartphones, the Galaxy Z Flip 5 and Galaxy Fold 5.

TITLE: Trump says 'we'll have fun' at 'trial of the century' as election case indictment looms
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is a target of a criminal probe by special counsel Jack Smith over efforts to reverse the 2020 electoral win of President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Britain's richest man says Brexit was 'not good for the UK,' backs PM Sunak's economic plans
SUMMARY: Britain's wealthiest man, Gopichand Hinduja, condemned the U.K.'s departure from the European Union, but threw his backing behind PM Rishi Sunak.

TITLE: Tesla under investigation by California attorney general over Autopilot safety, marketing
SUMMARY: The California attorney general is investigating Tesla over the electric car company's driver assistance technology, CNBC has learned.

TITLE: 'Barbie' box office dominance extends beyond the weekend
SUMMARY: "Barbie" continues to drive ticket sales at movie theaters following its historic opening weekend.

TITLE: Chipotle shares slide as sales fall short of Wall Street's expectations
SUMMARY: Chipotle's stock has climbed 50% year to date, but it fell after the company reported second quarter earnings.

TITLE: UK investigates weight loss, diabetes drugs like Wegovy and Ozempic for suicide risks
SUMMARY: The probe into potentially life-threatening side effects comes as the drugs skyrocket in popularity in the U.S. and draw heightened investor interest.

TITLE: Alphabet shares jump on beat and strong cloud growth
SUMMARY: The company reported strong growth in its cloud computing unit and announced a key executive would be moving to a new role.

TITLE: Meta, Microsoft and Amazon team up on maps project to crack Apple-Google duopoly
SUMMARY: Overture Maps Foundation is trying to collect enough data so that companies can build maps they own and operate rather than paying Google and Apple.

TITLE: Boeing’s Starliner losses total $1.5 billion with NASA astronauts still waiting to fly
SUMMARY: Since 2014, when NASA awarded Boeing with a fixed-price contract to develop Starliner, the company has recorded losses on the program almost every year.

TITLE: Hunter Biden pleads not guilty to charges after judge questions revised plea deal
SUMMARY: Judge Maryellen Noreika, an appointee of former President Donald Trump, put the proceedings on hold as she asked the parties to work out their dispute.

TITLE: She traveled to Japan more than 50 times. Here are 3 life habits she learned from the country
SUMMARY: "I became a person that I liked. This country changed my life," says Cheesie, a 39-year-old blogger from Malaysia.

TITLE: Rolls-Royce shares soar 19% after engine-maker raises guidance
SUMMARY: The company said it anticipates half-year profits, due out on Aug. 3, will be more than double market consensus.

TITLE: Amazon offers concessions to UK antitrust watchdog as part of probe into its marketplace practices
SUMMARY: Amazon on Wednesday offered commitments to the U.K. Competition and Markets Authority to address the British competition watchdog's concerns.

TITLE: Moody's sees 'significant risk' besieging Israel's economy
SUMMARY: Moody's Investors Service cautioned that "significant risk" looms over Israel's economy, after the passage of a law that curtails the Supreme Court's powers.

TITLE: Gap taps top Mattel executive to be its new CEO
SUMMARY: Richard Dickson, Mattel's president and chief operating officer credited with reviving the Barbie franchise, was selected to be Gap's new chief executive.

TITLE: Saudi soccer dominance could still take 'decades' despite reported $332 million Mbappé bid
SUMMARY: Saudi Arabian soccer club Al-Hilal has reportedly tabled a world record 300 million euro ($331.9 million) bid for Paris Saint-Germain star Kylian Mbappé.

TITLE: Boeing posts quarterly loss, but stock surges as aircraft deliveries drive up cash
SUMMARY: Boeing said Wednesday that it is transitioning to higher production of its bestselling Max aircraft, at a pace of 38 jets a month.
